Is it really an effective tool to reward people with a concert ticket to convince others of the importance of action, or is it just another form of so-called “clictivism” when people feel they have contributed to a case by signing an online petition or writing a Twitter post?
Since 2011, according to Global Citizen data, more than 19 million “actions” have been carried out by the project’s supporters, serving a wide variety of purposes.
