"With the support of the UK government and donors, national governments and global citizens like you, we can put social injustice and malnutrition in the footnotes of history books," Tracey Ullman, Power of Nutrition ambassador, told the crowd at a live concert in London in April 2018.
The group also claims that after asking the UK to improve the nutrition of mothers and their children in more than 5,000 actions, the government has allocated funds to the Power of Nutrition project, which will improve the nutrition of 5 million women and children.
One of the frequently asked questions posted on the Global Citizen website is “Why do you think extreme poverty can be eradicated?”.
